cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper deals with representation and reasoning of ontologies and rule languages for the semantic web, which falls under the scope of knowledge representation and reasoning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of computable set theory, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the consistency problem, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper provides a translation of rules belonging to the Semantic Web Rule Language (SWRL), which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
